The photophysical properties of RCDs @ PSI were analyzed as shown in Fig. 4
                        . The RCDs @ PSI powder showed broad peaks at 200–300 nm and 500–600 nm. In addition, the optimal FL emission peak of RCDs @ PSI at the optimal excitation (492 nm) was at 591 nm, and there was a shoulder peak at about 650 nm. This was similar to the optical properties of free RCDs (Fig. 5
                        ), indicating that the PL emission of RCDs @ PSI should come from RCDs. The RCDs @ PSI powder shows the maximum Phos wavelength at 754 nm under the excitation of 492 nm and also has a weak emission peak (λmax = 550 nm) in the range of 500–600 nm.To prove the inconsistency between the afterglow color (yellow-green) and the spectral (main emission λmax = 754 nm) emission of RCDs @ PSI, the afterglow spectra at different delay times were measured.
